      "id": 1030,
      "options": {
        "content": "## CI-CD JVM Internals \u2014 what this board shows & how to read it\nDeep-dive JVM telemetry for all Java microservices and the Jenkins controller, exported via the **OpenTelemetry Java agent** (zero-code instrumentation). All metrics follow the [OpenTelemetry JVM Semantic Conventions](https://opentelemetry.io/docs/specs/semconv/runtime/jvm-metrics/).\n\n| Section | What it answers |\n|---|---|\n| **Overview** | CPU utilization, heap used %, live threads, and GC overhead at a glance |\n| **Garbage Collection** | GC time/s, collection frequency, and pause p95/p99 per collector (SerialGC vs G1) |\n| **Heap & Non-Heap** | Used vs committed vs max for heap; metaspace + code-cache for non-heap |\n| **Memory Pools** | Per-pool breakdown (Eden / Survivor / Tenured / Metaspace / CodeHeap) |\n| **Buffers & advanced** | Direct/mapped NIO buffer pools; experimental runtime telemetry |\n| **HTTP response times** | Server-side latency p50/p95/p99 and request rate \u2014 correlate with GC pauses above |\n| **Logs & Traces** | Error/warn log stream and recent traces for the selected service |\n\n> **Tip:** Correlate a GC pause spike (*GC Pause p95/p99*) with a latency spike (*HTTP latency p50/p95/p99*) \u2014 they often land at the same timestamp.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "transparent": true,
      "type": "text"
    },
